This version of the code provies an implementation of the HPCG benchmark which
uses task dependency graphs to parallelize the SYMGS kernel on the finest level
of the grid and block coloring for the coarser levels. Merge of blocks is also
used to present a higher degree of vectorization, even though, no manual
vectorization is explicitly present on the code.

Only one specific rule must be fulfilled in order to run this code:

	* ny*nz % ((OMP_NUM_THREADS*2)/8) == 0

In order to compile this code, use the Makefile provided in:

	* setup/Make.ARM_TDG_BCOL

